what is the best way to get off birth control pills finish the entire pack stop in the middle i am wanting to get pregnant this october november i am hearing that it takes about to months after quitting to get pregnant would it make things easier if i quit my birth control pills in the middle of the pack instead of waiting to finish the entire pack no it would really be best if you go ahead and finish the pack then you will need to use a non hormonal method until you are ready to start trying i strongly recommend natural family planning as your method of birth control it will also make it easier once you start trying to get pregnant get the book taking charge of your fertility by toni weschler Fertility awareness Oral contraceptive Birth control Menstrual cycle Emergency contraception Pregnancy EastEnders Friends Breastfeeding Guinea pig USS Whale (SS-239) Depo Provera Endometriosis Tocopherol Coffee Urinary incontinence In vitro fertilisation Apollo 8 Ben Johnson (athlete) Tour de France Knots Landing Abortion debate Fox hunting Coitus interruptus The Amazing Race Abortion Textile manufacturing Psoriasis Elvis and Me Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Obstetrics Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Charmed Folic acid Neighbours Red Hot Chili Peppers Baldness treatments CPU design Sharon Tate USS Wahoo (SS-238) Survivor (novel) Spina bifida USS Atule (SS-403) Religion and abortion Buffalo Bills Organic farming The Inside Professional wrestling match types The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Dog training Toyota Prius Acne Emperor Xuan of Han Miscarriage Gray Wolf Lauren Bacall Alex Ferguson Fight Club Indianapolis 500 The Contender (television series) Tupac Shakur USS Thresher (SS-200) The Star Wars Holiday Special Mercury Atlas 6 Charles Manson USS Sea Dog (SS-401) Resident Evil Outbreak: File 2 GunZ The Duel Yom Kippur War Housebreaking Tobacco smoking 2005 Iditarod Rosa Parks 2004-05 in English football History of sex Pet Sounds Elephant Dance Dance Revolution ULTRAMIX 2 Batt